<dl id="n54146d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54146d">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54146d"> 146(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> this phallus, to increase / trade tourist <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54146d"><li>FW 76.34f </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/lexd.htm#n54146d">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/l39d.htm#n54146d">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54146d">MS BL 47476b-270</ms> </li><li>JJA 50:076 <a name="dd11" href="../../ff/fdra/dda.htm#dd11">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/d/dd11.htm#n54146d">Draft: I.4&sect;1.11</a>/2.11</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Dans d&apos;autres villages, le plus jeune fils, en succ&eacute;dant &agrave; son p&egrave;re dans sa maison, doit &eacute;lever un monolithe pour ses parents d&eacute;funts &mdash; ce qui correspond &agrave; ce que l&apos;on fait dans d&apos;autres villages, o&ugrave; des personnes particuli&egrave;rement prosp&egrave;res &eacute;rigent <mark>des monolithes</mark> de leur vivant, <mark>pour &laquo;intensifier&raquo; la prosp&eacute;rit&eacute; de la communaut&eacute;</mark> dans son ensemble. La signification de ces derniers monolithes est nettement <mark>phallique</mark>. <br><font color="green">[In other villages, the youngest son, succeeding his father in his house, must raise a monolith for his deceased parents - which corresponds to what one does in other villages, where particularly prosperous people erect monoliths during their lifetime, to "intensify" the prosperity of the community as a whole. The meaning of these latter monoliths is clearly phallic.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 209</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
